{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Banbury Cricket Club Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Bodicote]], [[Oxfordshire]] | establishment = 1997 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1997-present | club1 = [[Oxfordshire County Cricket Club|Oxfordshire]] | date = 16 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/290.html Ground profile }}
'''Banbury Cricket Club Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Bodicote]], [[Oxfordshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1997, when [[Oxfordshire County Cricket Club|Oxfordshire]] played their first [[Minor Counties Championship]] match on the ground against [[Dorset County Cricket Club|Dorset]]. From 1997 to present, the ground hosted 14 Minor Counties Championship matches<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/290_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on Banbury Cricket Club Ground]</ref> and 3 [[MCCA Knockout Trophy]] matches.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/290_mint.html Minor Counties Trophy Matches played on Banbury Cricket Club Ground]</ref>
The ground has held 2 [[List-A cricket|List-A]] matches, the first of which saw Oxfordshire play the [[Lancashire Cricket Board]] in the 1st round of the [[2003 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy]] which was played in 2002. The second List-A match came in the 1st round of the [[2004 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy]] with Oxfordshire playing [[Herefordshire County Cricket Club|Herefordshire]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/290_a.html List A Matches played on Banbury Cricket Club Ground]</ref>
In local domestic cricket, the ground is the home of [[Banbury Cricket Club]] who play in the [[Home Counties Premier Cricket League]].<ref>[http://www.banburycricketclub.co.uk/ Banbury Cricket Club]</ref>
