{{Use British English|date=July 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=March 2012}} {{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Sandygate Road | nickname = | image = [[File:HallamFCwithground.jpg|300px]] | caption = | fullname = | location = [[Crosspool]], [[Sheffield]] | broke_ground = | built = 1804 | opened = 1804 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Hallam F.C.]] | operator = [[Hallam F.C.]] | surface = grass | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor= | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = [[Hallam F.C.]], Hallam C.C.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hallamfc.net/pageID_3560807.html|title=Hallam Football Club|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070523073630/http://www.hallamfc.net/pageID_3560807.html|archivedate=23 May 2007|df=dmy-all}}</ref> | seating_capacity = 700 (210 seated, a further 40 covered)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hallamfc.net/pageID_3560837.html|title=Sandygate|publisher=Hallam Football Club|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070302133745/http://www.hallamfc.net/pageID_3560837.html|archivedate=2 March 2007|df=dmy-all}}</ref> | dimensions = }}
'''Sandygate Road''' is a [[football (soccer)|football]] and [[cricket]] stadium in the [[Sheffield]] [[districts of Sheffield|suburb]] of [[Crosspool]], [[South Yorkshire]], England. It is home to '''[[Hallam F.C.]]''' and '''Hallam C.C.'''
First opened in 1804, Hallam F.C. have played at the ground since 1860. Sandygate has been recognised by the ''[[Guinness Book of Records]]'' as the "Oldest Ground in the World".<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-south-yorkshire-23471740 | title=World's oldest football teams play in derby | publisher=bbc.co.uk | date=27 July 2013 | accessdate=30 September 2014}}</ref> On 26 December 1860, the world's first inter-club football match was played at the ground, Hallam taking on [[Sheffield F.C.]]
[[File:Guinnesrecord1.jpg|thumb|left|200px|The certificate for the record of being the oldest football ground in the world]]
