{{expand Swedish|Umeå Arena|date=August 2012}} {{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = T3 Center | former_names = Umeå Arena, SkyCom Arena, Umeå ishall | image = T3 Center, Umeå.jpg | location = [[Umeå]], [[Sweden]] | opened = 17 December 1963 | renovated = 2001 | owner = | tenants = | architect = | seating_capacity = 5,400 }} '''T3 Center''', formerly '''Umeå Arena''', '''SkyCom Arena''' and '''Umeå ishall''', is an indoor [[arena]] in [[Umeå]], [[Sweden]]. It is the home arena of the [[IF Björklöven]] and [[Tegs SK (ice hockey)|Tegs SK]] [[ice hockey]] teams. Its current capacity is 5,400 spectators.
The arena was first opened on 17 December 1963 as '''Umeå ishall'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://loven4ever.com/lucka-nr-17/|title=Lucka nr 17|publisher=Löven 4 Ever|language=Swedish|date=17 December 2009|accessdate=19 March 2018}}</ref> and rebuilt as Umeå Arena in 2001, which was the name until 2005. On 1 October 2008, the name was reverted to Umeå Arena after a new sponsor deal.<ref>{{cite press release |title=SkyCom Arena blir Umeå Arena |url=http://www.umea.se/pressmeddelandearkiv/pressmeddelanden/skycomarenablirumeaarena.5.1821d6e811c67c7e795800029698.html |publisher=[[Umeå Municipality]] |date=5 October 2008 |language=Swedish |accessdate=12 September 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110929011041/http://www.umea.se/pressmeddelandearkiv/pressmeddelanden/skycomarenablirumeaarena.5.1821d6e811c67c7e795800029698.html |archivedate=29 September 2011 |df= }}</ref>
On 17 September 2013, the arena was renamed '''T3 Center''' after the Swedish telecommunication company T3 bought the [[naming rights]] for at least the following five seasons (through the 2017–18 season).<ref>{{cite web |last=Ruuth |first=Tomas |title=Umeå Arena blir T3 Center |url=http://www.vk.se/992278/umea-arena-blir-t3-center |work=sportnu.se |language=Swedish |date=17 September 2013 |accessdate=21 April 2014}}</ref>
